---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout title="Greenland 2026" description="Plans and overview for our Greenland 2026 trip" pubDate={new Date('June 20 2026')}>
  <p>
    Welcome to the Greenland 2026 planning page. This is a living overview of our team's
    objectives, timeline and preparation for an expedition to Greenland in 2026. Short updates
    and trip journals will be posted on the main blog — see the blog for day-to-day updates.
  </p>

  <h2>Goals</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Conduct field observations of river and coastal bird habitats.</li>
    <li>Document kingfisher behaviour where observed and collect photographic records.</li>
    <li>Support conservation partners with on-the-ground surveys.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Timeline</h2>
  <p>
    Target departure: July 2026. Exact dates will be confirmed as permits and logistics are
    finalised. Preparatory work (permits, equipment checks, team training) takes place Spring 2026.
  </p>

  <h2>Planned Route & Activities</h2>
  <p>
    We'll be based from a small research camp with day trips to coastal and inland waterways.
    Activities include observation surveys, photo documentation, and collaboration with local
    researchers. Safety and low-impact practices are priorities.
  </p>

  <h2>Gear & Preparation</h2>
  <p>
    Key items: cold-weather clothing, waterproofs, binoculars, camera gear, GPS, first-aid kits,
    and communications equipment. We'll publish a detailed gear checklist on the blog ahead of
    departure.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact & Contributions</h2>
  <p>
    If you'd like to contribute, follow the blog for updates and contact details. We appreciate
    help with local knowledge, equipment sponsorship, and conservation partnerships.
  </p>

  <p>
    Note: For short updates and trip logs, check the <a href="/blog">blog</a> — this Greenland
    page is intended as the expedition's home and planning summary.
  </p>
</Layout>
